OL,3,CWinter Solstice: The shortest day of
OL,4,Cthe year has arrived
OL,6,FThe solstices mark the times during
OL,7,Fthe year when the Earth is at its most
OL,8,Fextreme tilt toward or away from the
OL,9,Fsun.
OL,11,FScientists don't know exactly why our
OL,12,Fplanet became tilted on its axis, but
OL,13,Fsome theories suggest it was knocked
OL,14,Foff balance by a huge collision.
OL,16,FDuring the Northern Hemisphere's
OL,17,Fwinter solstice, the upper half of the
OL,18,FEarth is tilted away from the sun,
OL,19,Fcreating the shortest day and longest
OL,20,Fnight of the year. The winter solstice
OL,21,Ffalls between December 20 and 23.
